definition.value: Zone of kidney located at its superior end. Examples: There is only one superior pole of kidney.
Zone of kidney located at its inferior end. Examples: There is only one inferior pole of kidney.
Organ segment in the kidney defined by the distribution of the segmental renal arteries.
Renal segment supplied by the superior segmental renal artery.
Renal segment supplied by the anterior superior segmental renal artery.
Renal segment supplied by the anterior inferior segmental renal artery.
Renal segment supplied by the inferior segmental renal artery.
Renal segment supplied by the posterior segmental renal artery.
